Section Header: Protocol deviations are classified as minor or major. Major protocol deviations are a subset of protocol deviations that significantly affect the completeness, accuracy, and/or integrity of the study data or that significantly affect a subject's rights, safety, or welfare. See CRO guidance document for further details.

Section Header:
Reminder:
Safety Follow-up: 100 days (+ 14 day reporting window) from their last dose of study drug or within 7 days before initiation of a new antineoplastic treatment (whichever comes first). 

Clinical Follow-up: Subjects who discontinue without disease progression. Visits will occur every 12 weeks (+/- 2 weeks) until: 1) start of a new antineoplastic therapy, 2) disease progression, 3) death, 4) withdrawal of consent, or 5) study closure, whichever occurs first. 

Survival Follow-up: Subjects who discontinue treatment and have disease progression should be contacted every 12 weeks (+/- 2 weeks).
